    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/ 180\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Put a large baking tray (or two) in the oven to heat up (this will stop your <strong>pizza bottom[s]</strong> from going soggy!)</p><p>Meanwhile, finely slice your <strong>baby button mushrooms</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sausage-and-mushroom-pizza-with-garlic-and-herb-dip/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>sausage meat </strong>(remove the paper if required!), breaking it up into small pieces with a wooden spoon as you go</p><p>Cook for 3 min or until the sausage meat has browned slightly</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sausage-and-mushroom-pizza-with-garlic-and-herb-dip/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the sausage meat has browned, add the <strong>sliced mushrooms</strong> and cook for 2 min further until the mushrooms have started to caramelise (no pink meat!)\u2013 this is your <strong>sausage & mushroom mixture</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sausage-and-mushroom-pizza-with-garlic-and-herb-dip/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>tomato paste</strong> to a bowl with <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)<strong> </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, <strong>pepper</strong> and <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Add 5 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[7 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[10 tbsp] </span><strong>cold water</strong> and stir it all together \u2013 this is your <strong>tomato sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sausage-and-mushroom-pizza-with-garlic-and-herb-dip/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Drain your <strong>mozzarella</strong>, then pat and squeeze as much liquid out as you can with kitchen paper</p><p>Tear the <strong>drained mozzarella</strong> into rough, bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sausage-and-mushroom-pizza-with-garlic-and-herb-dip/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Remove the heated tray[s] from the oven and add your <strong>pizza base[s]</strong></p><p>Divide the <strong>tomato sauce</strong> between the pizza base[s] and spread evenly all over them with the back of a spoon</p><p>Top with the <strong>torn mozzarella</strong> and <strong>sausage & mushroom mixture</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 13-15 min or until the mozzarella has melted and the pizza base[s] is crisp</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sausage-and-mushroom-pizza-with-garlic-and-herb-dip/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the pizza is cooking, combine the <strong>remaining chopped garlic</strong> (not a big garlic fan? Try using less!) with your <strong>mayo</strong>, <strong>dried oregano</strong>, 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil </strong>in a small bowl<strong> </strong>\u2013<strong> </strong>this is your <strong>garlic & herb dip</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sausage-and-mushroom-pizza-with-garlic-and-herb-dip/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> sausage & mushroom pizza</strong> with the<strong> garlic & herb dip</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
